Cameron Hooker was handed a 104-year sentence in 1985 for the kidnap, torture and rape of Colleen Stan . 
  Stan was known as 'the Girl in the Box' after she was forced into a coffin-like structure for 23 hours a day during much of her captivity . 
  Despite his century-long jail term he was allowed to request parole seven years earlier than under the normal rules . 
  But the parole board has denied his request and said he is 'far from suitable' for release . 
  Stan had been hitchhiking in California when she was kidnapped . 
  She was tortured, raped and left for days in a head box . 
  Hooker kept her as a sex slave for seven years . 
 